<item>
            <title>[SEC-2549] java.lang.IllegalAccessError: class org.springframework.security.config.annotation.authentication.configuration.$Proxy90 cannot access its superinterface &lt;omitted&gt;.AuthenticationConfiguration$LazyBean</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-2549</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Is it possible to change the visibility of LazyBean marker interface to `public`?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are planning to pull up spring dependencies as JBoss EAP &quot;module&quot; (shared libraries) to be shared among all of our applications.&lt;br/&gt;
Each &quot;module&quot; has its own isolated ClassLoader, and is parallel to the war &quot;module&quot; ClassLoader, so we have to emulate the class loading hierarchy ourselves for compatibility.&lt;br/&gt;
The problem is that the aggregated ClassLoader (delegates to &quot;module&quot; classLoader and then the applications&apos;s ClassLoader) cannot sees the private LazyBean marker.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>JBoss EAP 6.1.1</environment>
