                                        <comments>
                            <comment id="101477" author="tan9" created="Mon, 7 Apr 2014 01:46:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If we set beanClassLoader to the module&apos;s classLoader, we cannot load beans form our application.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="101489" author="rwinch" created="Mon, 7 Apr 2014 06:30:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d really prefer to avoid making the interface public. I will need to do some investigation on my part to determine what our options are.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="101506" author="tan9" created="Mon, 7 Apr 2014 10:28:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The private marker interface can only be seen by the exact classLoader.&lt;br/&gt;
Can we just specifies to the classLoader which loaded AuthenticationConfiguration or some other classes in the same jar while initializing?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="102429" author="rwinch" created="Thu, 24 Apr 2014 12:03:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I resolved this issue by removing the LazyBean interface all together. If you are interested in the details you can refer to commit &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/commit/5e88ebef2e973d4734cc30a392d1a7ec15e97b17&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;5e88ebe&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix should now be available in 3.2.4.CI-SNAPSHOT in the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/wiki/Spring-repository-FAQ#what-repositories-are-available&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;spring snapshot repository&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href=&quot;http://repo.spring.io/snapshot/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://repo.spring.io/snapshot/&lt;/a&gt;). Can you please try this out and see if it resolves your issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="102484" author="tan9" created="Fri, 25 Apr 2014 10:07:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can confirm that this issue has been fixed in current snapshot release, thank you very much!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="102485" author="rwinch" created="Fri, 25 Apr 2014 10:09:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for taking the time to submit the issue and for the quick response!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
